direct the Solid Waste Management Board to regularly conduct meetings for the formulation of worthwhile projects/programs/activities and monitoring mechanisms to improve compliance rate by the households on the ordinances passed to implement the Ecological Waste Management Act of 2000;
reduce the huge budget for the salaries of job order personnel so as to provide allocations for other equally important SW priority programs and projects;
firmly impose fines and penalties against violators of prohibited acts to improve compliance rate and to provide sufficient funding for solid waste management activities;
educate the public through the conduct of continuous forums and seminars to raise awareness and increase the compliance rate of households and residents; and
devise ways to improve the system of collection and disposal of garbage and wastes.

